-- Wall Street Was `Flying Blind' With Credit Derivatives, Angelides Says
-- Hugh Son
-- 2010-06-30T13:10:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/wall-street-was-flying-blind-with-credit-derivatives-angelides-says.html

          
          
             Securities firms and regulators were
uninformed about the risk of derivatives that contributed to the
credit freeze in 2008, the chairman of the Financial Crisis
Inquiry Commission said.  
 “When clarity mattered most, Wall Street and Washington
were flying blind,” Chairman  Phil Angelides  said today in
opening remarks of a hearing into derivatives.  
